{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d34-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6321"},"text":"§ 6321.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Findings; purpose; definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d35-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Findings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Congress finds that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d36-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the development and implementation by States of laws, policies, programs, and procedures to conserve and to improve efficiency in the use of energy will have an immediate and substantial effect in reducing the rate of growth of energy demand and in minimizing the adverse social, economic, political, and environmental impacts of increasing energy consumption;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d37-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the development and implementation of energy conservation programs by States will most efficiently and effectively minimize any adverse economic or employment impacts of changing patterns of energy use and meet local economic, climatic, geographic, and other unique conditions and requirements of each State; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d38-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Federal Government has a responsibility to foster and promote comprehensive energy conservation programs and practices by establishing guidelines for such programs and providing overall coordination, technical assistance, and financial support for specific State initiatives in energy conservation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d39-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Purpose","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It is the purpose of this part to promote the conservation of energy and reduce the rate of growth of energy demand by authorizing the Secretary to establish procedures and guidelines for the development and implementation of specific State energy conservation programs and to provide Federal financial and technical assistance to States in support of such programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this part:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appliance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “appliance” means any article, such as a room air-conditioner, refrigerator-freezer, or dishwasher, which the Secretary classifies as an appliance for purposes of this part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Building","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “building” means any structure which includes provision for a heating or cooling system, or both, or for a hot water system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Energy audit","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “energy audit” means any process which identifies and specifies the energy and cost savings which are likely to be realized through the purchase and installation of particular energy conservation measures or renewable-resource energy measures and which—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is carried out in accordance with rules of the Secretary; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d3f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" imposes—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d40-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/3/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" no direct costs, with respect to individuals who are occupants of dwelling units in any State having a supplemental State energy conservation plan; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d41-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/3/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" only reasonable costs, as determined by the Secretary, with respect to any person not described in clause (i).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Rules referred to in subparagraph (A) may include minimum qualifications for, and provisions with respect to conflicts of interest of, persons carrying out such energy audits.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d42-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Energy conservation measure","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “energy conservation measure” means a measure which modifies any building, building system, energy consuming device associated with the building, or industrial plant, the construction of which has been completed prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-05-01"},"text":"May 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":", if such measure has been determined by means of an energy audit or by the Secretary, by rule under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6325/e/1"},"text":"section 6325(e)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", to be likely to maintain or improve the efficiency of energy use and to reduce energy costs (as calculated on the basis of energy costs reasonably projected over time, as determined by the Secretary) in an amount sufficient to enable a person to recover the total cost of purchasing and installing such measure (without regard to any tax benefit or Federal financial assistance applicable thereto) within the period of—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d43-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the useful life of the modification involved, as determined by the Secretary, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d44-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 15 years after the purchase and installation of such measure,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"whichever is less. Such term does not include (i) the purchase or installation of any appliance, (ii) any conversion from one fuel or source of energy to another which is of a type which the Secretary, by rule, determines is ineligible on the basis that such type of conversion is inconsistent with national policy with respect to energy conservation or reduction of imports of fuels, or (iii) any measure, or type of measure, which the Secretary determines does not have as its primary purpose an improvement in efficiency of energy use.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d45-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Industrial plant","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “industrial plant” means any fixed equipment or facility which is used in connection with, or as part of, any process or system for industrial production or output.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d46-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Public building","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “public building” means any building which is open to the public during normal business hours.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d47-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Renewable-resource energy measure","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “renewable-resource energy measure” means a measure which modifies any building or industrial plant, the construction of which has been completed prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-08-14"},"text":"August 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", if such measure has been determined by means of an energy audit or by the Secretary, by rule under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6325/e/1"},"text":"section 6325(e)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", to—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d48-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/7/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" involve changing, in whole or in part, the fuel or source of the energy used to meet the requirements of such building or plant from a depletable source of energy to a nondepletable source of energy; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d49-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/7/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" be likely to reduce energy costs (as calculated on the basis of energy costs reasonably projected over time, as determined by the Secretary) in an amount sufficient to enable a person to recover the total cost of purchasing and installing such measure (without regard to any tax benefit or Federal financial assistance applicable thereto) within the period of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d4a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/7/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the useful life of the modification involved, as determined by the Secretary, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d4b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/7/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 25 years after the purchase and installation of such measure,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"whichever is less.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"Such term does not include the purchase or installation of any appliance.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d4c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6321/c/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transportation controls","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “transportation controls” means any plan, procedure, method, or arrangement, or any system of incentives, disincentives, restrictions, and requirements, which is designed to reduce the amount of energy consumed in transportation, except that the term does not include rationing of gasoline or diesel fuel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbd978d4d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/163/tIII/s361"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–163, title III, § 361","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/932"},"text":"89 Stat. 932","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/619/tVI/s691/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–619, title VI, § 691(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-09"},"text":"Nov. 9, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3288"},"text":"92 Stat. 3288","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/dD/tI/s40108/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, div. D, title I, § 40108(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-11-15"},"text":"Nov. 15, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/941"},"text":"135 Stat. 941","children":[],"tail":", 942.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbd978d4e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbd978d4f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbd978d50-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (1) to (8) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6326"},"text":"section 6326 of this title","children":[],"tail":", which were transferred to subsec. (c) of this section by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/dD/tI/s40108/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, div. D, title I, § 40108(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-11-15"},"text":"Nov. 15, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/942"},"text":"135 Stat. 942","children":[],"tail":", were based on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/163/tIII/s366"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–163, title III, § 366","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/935"},"text":"89 Stat. 935","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/385/tIV/s431"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–385, title IV, § 431","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-08-14"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1158"},"text":"90 Stat. 1158","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/619/tVI/s691/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–619, title VI, § 691(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-09"},"text":"Nov. 9, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3288"},"text":"92 Stat. 3288","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/440/s2/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–440, § 2(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1006"},"text":"104 Stat. 1006","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/dD/tI/s40108/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, div. D, title I, § 40108(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-11-15"},"text":"Nov. 15, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/941"},"text":"135 Stat. 941","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbd978d51-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s40108/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 40108(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Findings; purpose; definitions” for “Congressional findings and declaration of purpose” in section catchline and, in subsec. (a), inserted heading and substituted “Congress” for “The Congress” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s40108/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 40108(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted heading."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s40108/a/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 40108(a)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1) to (8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/s40108/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, § 40108(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", transferred pars. (1) to (8) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6326"},"text":"section 6326 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to subsec. (c) of this section. See Codification note above."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/619"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–619","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”, meaning Administrator of the Federal Energy Administration."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbd978d52-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbd978d53-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Wage Rate Requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58","children":[],"tail":", including authority of Secretary of Labor, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s18851"},"text":"section 18851 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbd978d54-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Report on Coordination of Energy Conservation Programs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/619/tVI/s623"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–619, title VI, § 623","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-09"},"text":"Nov. 9, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3283"},"text":"92 Stat. 3283","children":[],"tail":", provided that not later than 6 months after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-09"},"text":"Nov. 9, 1978","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary of Energy submit a report on the coordination of Federal energy conservation programs involving State and local government."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
